# Design System & Themes

Visual language for **Orbit** — cinematic, dark, controller-first, optimized for TV/couch distance.
Inspired by PS5, Nintendo Switch, and Apple TV launchers.

User-facing theme authoring guide: [docs/THEMES.md](THEMES.md).
Example theme: [docs/examples/arcade-neon.json](examples/arcade-neon.json).

---

## Brand

- **Product name:** Orbit
- **Typography:** DM Sans (display + body) — loaded globally via CSS
- **Tone:** cinematic dark, glass panels, bold focus rings, minimal chrome
- **Target:** fullscreen macOS desktop, viewed from couch distance

---

## Theme system

Themes are JSON definitions that drive **colors, radii, motion, background style, and entire layout**.

### Built-in themes

Defined in `src/themes/types.ts` (`BUILT_IN_THEMES`):

| ID | Name | Layout | Character |
| -- | ---- | ------ | --------- |
| `orbit` | Orbit Default | `orbit` | Hero rows + cinematic scrim |
| `ps5` | PlayStation 5 | `ps5` | Immersive artwork, circular tiles, glass |
| `switch-2` | Switch 2 | `switch` | Square tiles, bottom dock |

### Custom themes

Drop `.json` files into:

```text
~/Library/Application Support/Orbit/themes/
```

Loaded via Tauri `list_custom_themes`. Reload from **Settings → Reload custom themes**.

Custom themes with the same `id` as a built-in theme override the built-in entry.

---

## Color tokens

Colors are **space-separated RGB channels** (no commas) — applied as CSS variables:

```css
--orbit-canvas: 5 7 12;
background: rgb(var(--orbit-canvas));
```

| Token | CSS variable | Usage |
| ----- | ------------ | ----- |
| `canvas` | `--orbit-canvas` | App background |
| `surface` | `--orbit-surface` | Inputs / nested surfaces |
| `panel` | `--orbit-panel` | Cards and glass panels |
| `foreground` | `--orbit-foreground` | Primary text |
| `muted` | `--orbit-muted` | Secondary text |
| `accent` | `--orbit-accent` | CTA / highlights |
| `focus` | `--orbit-focus` | Controller focus ring |
| `border` | `--orbit-border` | Subtle borders |

Applied at runtime by `theme.store.ts` when user selects a theme.

### Theme JSON shape

```typescript
interface ThemeDefinition {
  id: string
  name: string
  description?: string
  author?: string
  fonts?: { display?: string; body?: string }
  colors: ThemeColors
  radius?: string
  cardRadius?: string
  blur?: string
  backgroundStyle?: string   // radial | ps5 | switch
  layout?: 'orbit' | 'ps5' | 'switch'
  motion?: { duration?: string; easing?: string }
}
```

See [docs/THEMES.md](THEMES.md) for authoring walkthrough.

